A center where youths seeking for employment will be converging to get the latest information on available opportunities in the world of business is to be established in Nairobi. The job Centre would be used to guide the youths in the process of registering a business. It will also help them in accessing information on what they require to do business with the government. Business development workshops and seminars will be organized for the job seekers at the center, which according to Kenya national chamber of commerce and industry (KNCCI) in Nairobi county is meant to help in establishing and expanding opportunities for micro and small enterprise or MSEâ€™s